"""MODULE.bazel for the GoogleSQL prebuilt artifact.

Pinned by tools/googlesql-prebuilt/package.sh. Placeholders ({{...}})
are substituted at package time with the artifact's actual versions so
consumer-wiring callers can match Bzlmod dep pins to the source build's
MODULE.bazel.

Naming (compatibility-surface clarification, see
tools/googlesql-prebuilt/README.md "Naming clarification"):

- Tarball top-level directory  : `googlesql_prebuilt_linux_amd64/` (compatibility-surface freeze).
- GitHub Release asset name    : `googlesql-prebuilt-linux-amd64-...` (artifact-producer contract).
- Module name in MODULE.bazel  : `googlesql` (the consumer-facing identity).

Why the module name is `googlesql` and not `googlesql_prebuilt_linux_amd64`:
the emulator's `BUILD.bazel` files reference `@googlesql//googlesql/public:*`
and `@googlesql//googlesql/resolved_ast:*` directly. Those references
are frozen by the compatibility surface (label-inventory.md) and must
not change between source mode and prebuilt mode. By declaring this
artifact's MODULE.bazel identity as `googlesql`, a consumer can flip
between source mode (the existing `local_path_override` to
`../googlesql`) and prebuilt mode
(`--override_module=googlesql=<unpacked_artifact_path>` or an
equivalent `archive_override`) without editing any emulator BUILD file.

The consumer-wiring track owns the consumer-side wiring; this file
declares what the prebuilt repo NEEDS at compile + link time. The
header tree under
`include/googlesql/...` `#include`s symbols from these third-party
trees, and the static archives in `lib/` (linked at producer-side
build time) carry unresolved external references into them, so the
consumer's link must see the same versions.
"""

module(
    name = "googlesql",
    version = "{{ARTIFACT_VERSION}}",
)

# Mirrors the source-side //MODULE.bazel pins. Mismatches between the
# consumer's resolved version and these declarations are a safety-gate
# parity error: the static archives in lib/ were linked against these
# exact versions, so resolving a different version would produce
# multiple-definition link errors or ODR violations at runtime.
bazel_dep(name = "rules_cc", version = "0.2.8")
bazel_dep(name = "abseil-cpp", version = "{{ABSEIL_VERSION}}", repo_name = "com_google_absl")
bazel_dep(name = "protobuf", version = "{{PROTOBUF_VERSION}}", repo_name = "com_google_protobuf")
bazel_dep(name = "grpc", version = "{{GRPC_VERSION}}", repo_name = "com_github_grpc_grpc")

# Third-party deps reached transitively from the artifact's exported
# header tree. Discovered during consumer-wiring verification when prebuilt
# mode tried to compile a consumer TU that pulled the `:type` wrapper:
# `googlesql/public/types/...` -> `googlesql/common/multiprecision_int.h`
# -> `googlesql/base/bits.h` `#include`s `gtest/gtest_prod.h`, and
# `googlesql/public/value.h` includes the same.
# `googlesql/base/exactfloat.h` reaches `openssl/bn.h`,
# `googlesql/public/functions/regexp.h` reaches `re2/re2.h`. Without
# these `bazel_dep`s the prebuilt repo's wrapper compiles fail under
# strict-deps + sandboxing because the third-party headers are not in
# any `cc_library`'s `hdrs` reachable from the wrapper.
#
# Versions match the ones GoogleSQL itself pins in its
# `MODULE.bazel`, so the static archives shipped under `lib/` carry
# unresolved externals into the same ABI the consumer's build
# resolves to.
#
# `repo_name` aliases match what GoogleSQL's `BUILD` files reference
# (`@com_google_googletest//:gtest`, `@com_googlesource_code_re2//:re2`,
# `@boringssl//:crypto`).
bazel_dep(name = "googletest", version = "{{GOOGLETEST_VERSION}}", repo_name = "com_google_googletest")
bazel_dep(name = "re2", version = "{{RE2_VERSION}}", repo_name = "com_googlesource_code_re2")
bazel_dep(name = "boringssl", version = "{{BORINGSSL_VERSION}}")

# Googleapis is needed for the well-known `google.type` protos
# (`google.type.Date`, `google.type.TimeOfDay`, etc.) that GoogleSQL's
# datetime functions reference at link time. The static archives in
# `lib/` carry unresolved `google::type::_Date_default_instance_` /
# `google::type::Date::GetMetadata() const` symbols that the consumer
# must resolve through this `bazel_dep`. Versions match upstream
# GoogleSQL's `MODULE.bazel` so the proto codegen ABI is identical to
# the producer-side build.
#
# The `:date_cc_proto` / `:timeofday_cc_proto` targets are listed on
# the `:_all_hdrs` cc_library in `BUILD.bazel` so consumers
# transitively pick them up at link time via the wrapper deps.
bazel_dep(name = "googleapis", version = "{{GOOGLEAPIS_VERSION}}", repo_name = "com_google_googleapis")
bazel_dep(name = "googleapis-cc", version = "{{GOOGLEAPIS_CC_VERSION}}")

# ICU + farmhash + differential-privacy are statically bundled into
# `lib/libgooglesql.a` (their object code is appended to the archive
# by `tools/googlesql-prebuilt/package.sh`), so they do NOT appear as
# `bazel_dep`s here. The manifest's `bundled_thirdparty_deps`
# enumerates the bundled versions for source-vs-prebuilt parity
# checking (the safety-gate parity check). Rationale:
#
#   - Upstream GoogleSQL fetches ICU via its own
#     `googlesql/bazel/http_archive_deps.bzl` extension at the pinned
#     `release-76-1/icu4c-76_1-src.tgz` tarball with a custom BUILD
#     file. The closest BCR module (`icu 78.x`) uses an incompatible
#     `icu_78::` namespace versioning vs. the producer-side `icu_76::`
#     symbols carried by the bundled object code.
#   - Farmhash is not published in the Bazel Central Registry. Upstream
#     GoogleSQL fetches it via http_archive at a pinned commit.
#   - Differential-privacy (the C++ library + its protos, plus the
#     cephes inverse-gaussian helper) is also not in BCR. GoogleSQL's
#     anonymization / DP-aware aggregate functions in
#     `googlesql/reference_impl/...` reference these symbols at link
#     time, so the bundled archive carries them too.
#
# See `docs/dev/googlesql-prebuilt/headers-and-libraries.md` for the
# bundle / consumer-resolved boundary; see `upgrade-rules.md` for the
# procedure to add to or remove from `bundled_thirdparty_deps`.
